.TH "of_pm_clk_add_clks" 9 "of_pm_clk_add_clks" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
of_pm_clk_add_clks \- Start using device clock(s) for power management.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" of_pm_clk_add_clks
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
Device whose clock(s) is going to be used for power management.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Add a series of clocks described in the 'clocks' device-tree node for
a device to the list of clocks used for the power management of \fIdev\fP.
On success, returns the number of clocks added. Returns a negative
error code if there are no clocks in the device node for the device
or if adding a clock fails.
